model.group
Class Seminar

java.lang.Object
  model.group.Seminar
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class Seminar
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

The Seminar class represents seminar entities, that include basic information about a seminar.

The Seminar class implements Serializable interface, which makes it allowed to write into files by ObjectOutputStream.

See Also:
Serializable, Serialized Form

Initialises a newly created Seminar object with attributes of the passed parameters.

Parameters:
seminarID - ID of a seminar, which is the primary key of Seminar, and is allocated by system automatically.
topic - Topic of a seminar
time - Time of seminar that will be hold
date - Date of seminar that will be hold
place - Place of seminar that will be hold
groupNumber - Number of the group this seminar belongs to. It is the same with the coordinator's group number.
